        {
            "id": "https://tinkermeer.github.io/sungjilee.github.io/memory-cube-5.html",
            "url": "https://tinkermeer.github.io/sungjilee.github.io/memory-cube-5.html",
            "title": "Alone, not alone",
            "summary": "This work captures moments of video conversations with my father, whom I am unable to meet in person. Feelings of longing and emotional&hellip;",
            "content_html": "\n  <p>\n    This work captures moments of video conversations with my father, whom I am unable to meet in person. Feelings of longing and emotional absence lead me to stitch into an old, empty cellphone case.<br>Through weaving and stitching, I attempt to bridge the distance between past and present. The repetitive act of sewing becomes a way of revisiting memories while confronting his physical absence. The cellphone case, once an object of communication, is transformed into a space where memory, loss, and connection coexist.\n  </p>",
            "image": "https://tinkermeer.github.io/sungjilee.github.io/media/posts/25/Lee_hi-dad.jpg",
            "author": {
                "name": "sj"
